subSubSection.paragraph:
Axis. The surface of the axis is smooth (
Fig. 32C
). There are no rounded pits on the surface of the axis at the position of each autozooids. The burrows of commensal organisms are found on the surface of the axis (
Fig. 32B
).

Coenenchyme. Coenenchyme is too thin to be measured. The surface is smooth and small warts are not remarkable (
Fig. 33
).

Color. The dry coenenchyme is pale pink. The axes are pink to pale red in color (
Fig. 32
).
